==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Monteith
<hw>Mon*teith"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A kind of cotton
handkerchief having a uniform colored ground with a regular pattern of
white spots produced by discharging the color; -- so called from the
Glasgow manufactures.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Monte-jus</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Monteith
<hw>Mon*teith"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>
}</mhw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A vessel in which glasses are washed; -- so
called from the name of the inventor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>New things produce new words, and thus <qex>Monteth</qex>⟦br⟧
Has by one vessel saved his name from death.</q>
<rj><qau>King.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Montgolfier</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
